I would like to thank Jaroslav Polasek and Volker Hergert for the their contributions to this issue of beatochess. Jaroslav pointed out an error on my part in the last issue and sent me his own correction of the Isenegger +0612.10g2e2 (1944) study. As you can see below, Volker was very busy in commenting and revising studies.

For this issue my focus has been on commenting and revising studies by Isenegger that have been included in Harolds HHdbVI database. You can access the pgn file of all his studies, including the findings in beatochess-13/14, here:

Isenegger-studies

1 beatochess-13: erratum

1.1 Isenegger +0612.10g2e2 (1944) corrections

Jaroslav Polasek (JP) informed me that my correction of the Isenegger +0612.10 study is not correct. I checked this and realized that I picked the wrong study.

Below are all corrections: the one I intended for beatochess-13, the one by Volker (from beatochess-13), and a new one kindly provided by Jaroslav. Jaroslav also informed me that he is working on a version with richter content, which he will publish in EG. Stay tuned

GBR: +0612.10f2c1 (c) FEN: 8/1r3N2/6P1/7r/8/6B1/5KN1/2k5 w - - 0 1

correction: Neuenschwander=B beatochess 10/11/2025. 1. Bf4+ Kb1 2. g7 Rg5 3. Bxg5 Rxf7+ 4. Bf6 Rxf6+ 5. Nf4 Rxf4+ 6. Kg3 Rf1 7. Kg2 (7. Kh2 or ) 1-0.

GBR: +0612.20g2b8 (c) FEN: 1k2r3/4P3/7P/1r5N/4N1B1/8/6K1/8 w - - 0 1

correction: Hergert=V beatochess 30/10/2025. 1. Ng7! Rxe7 2. h7 Rh5! 3. Bxh5 (3. Nxh5? Rxh7!1) 3 Rxg7+ 4. Ng5! (4. Ng3? Rxh7!1) 4 Rxg5+ 5. Bg4! Rxg4+ 6. Kh3 1-0.

GBR: +0612.10g2e2 (c) FEN: 8/4r1N1/7P/8/8/7B/4kNK1/2r5 w - - 0 1

correction: Polasek=J beatochess 10/11/2025. 1. Bg4+ Kd2 2. h7 Rc8 3. Ne4+ Kc1 4. Bxc8 Rxg7+ 5. Ng5 Rxg5+ 6. Bg4 Rxg4+ 7. Kh3 Rg1 8. Kh2 1-0.

2.1.4 Isenegger +0032.23b8f7 (1941). Changed solution

For me the two knight sacrifices is the theme, the rest is of no particular interest. The study is correct if one ends the study after move 3. Very short solutions are not uncommon in Iseneggers studies.

2.1.6 Isenegger =0000.12b5e5 (1941). Cooks or (minor) duals?

For me the clou is the first move. In the play afterwards White can switch the move order, but the way to a draw remains the same. So I would demote Rainers cooks to duals or minor duals.
